[2026-07-14] [Ask My Docs / Citations] — Finding, not a decision: the Block 5 real-corpus spot-check (all 8 design-doc questions) landed at coverage=1.0 on every question — no citation was naturally stripped in this batch, because Block 4's own prompt fix already filters most bad citations upstream. The fail-safe stripping path itself is proven only by Chunk 5.4's dedicated adversarial live-API test (stall001 kept, unrelated1 stripped, coverage 0.5), not by this organic spot-check. Logged as evidence that a non-adversarial spot-check and a targeted negative-case test verify different things.
